\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Each block can configure any of these settings separately, providing a more fine-grained control over what exists via 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 add_theme_support
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 . The settings declared at the top-level affect to all blocks, unless a particular block overwrites it. It\'92s a way to provide inheritance and configure all blocks at once.\
Note, however, that not all settings are relevant for all blocks. The settings section provides an opt-in/opt-out mechanism for themes, but it\'92s the block\'92s responsibility to add support for the features that are relevant to it. For example, if a block doesn\'92t implement the 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 dropCap
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3  feature, a theme can\'92t enable it for such a block through 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 theme.json
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 \ul \ulc2 Opt-in into UI controls
\f3\b \cf2 \cb3 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 There\'92s one special setting property, 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 appearanceTools
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 , which is a boolean and its default value is false. Themes can use this setting to enable the following ones:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa425\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \ul \ulc2 Backward compatibility with add_theme_support
\f3\b \cf2 \cb3 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 To retain backward compatibility, the existing 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 add_theme_support
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3  declarations that configure the block editor are retrofit in the proper categories for the top-level section. For example, if a theme uses 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 add_theme_support('disable-custom-colors')
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 , it\'92ll be the same as setting 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 settings.color.custom
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3  to 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 false
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 . If the 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 theme.json
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3  contains any settings, these will take precedence over the values declared via 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 add_theme_support
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 . This is the complete list of equivalences:\

