\f1\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 \ul \ulc2 Styles
\f3\b \cf2 \cb3 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Each block declares which style properties it exposes via the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/reference-guides/block-api/block-supports/"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \cb3 \ul \ulc2 block supports mechanism}}. The support declarations are used to automatically generate the UI controls for the block in the editor. Themes can use any style property via the 
\f2\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cf2 \cb3 theme.json
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3  for any block \uc0\u8213  it\'92s the theme\'92s responsibility to verify that it works properly according to the block markup, etc.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf5 \cb3 \{\
    "version": 3,\
    "styles": \{\
        "border": \{\
            "radius": "value",\
            "color": "value",\
            "style": "value",\
            "width": "value"\
        \},\
        "filter": \{\
            "duotone": "value"\
        \},\
        "color": \{\
            "background": "value",\
            "gradient": "value",\
            "text": "value"\
